  <brief_title>Understanding GMK Sphere Implant Tibiofemoral Kinematics by Means of Dynamic Videofluoroscopy</brief_title>
  <official_title>Understanding GMK Sphere Implant Tibiofemoral Kinematics by Means of Dynamic Videofluoroscopy</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Medacta International SA</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Medacta International SA</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this research project is to perform a comparative study on the in vivo
      kinematics of the GMK Sphere prosthesis in comparison to the conventional GMK PS Fixed
      Bearing TKA and the GMK UC Fixed Bearing TKA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
